        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(compaction): add identifier survival validation after summarization",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nImprove compaction identifier survival with transcript-wide extraction and quality-guard retry hints. Fixes two security/correctness issues found during review:\n\n**Fix 1 — Sanitize string-encoded JSON arguments before extraction**: `extractMessageTextForIdentifiers` now parses string-encoded tool arguments as JSON and passes the parsed object through `sanitizeDiagnosticPayload` before identifier scanning. Previously, string arguments (e.g. OpenAI's JSON-stringified format) were appended raw, allowing credential values like `{\"token\":\"deadbeef12345678\"}` to feed the hex identifier extractor and leak into `## Exact identifiers`.\n\n**Fix 2 — Fail strict compaction when cap recovery cannot fit**: When strict mode detects that final capping removed required identifiers and the recovery block would exceed `MAX_COMPACTION_SUMMARY_CHARS`, compaction is now cancelled instead of returning a summary with known identifier loss. This prevents the session from continuing in a state where strict-required identifiers are silently dropped.\n\n## Changed files\n\n- `src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard-quality.ts` — Parse string args as JSON, sanitize via `sanitizeDiagnosticPayload` before appending; non-JSON strings still pass through\n- `src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard.ts` — Cancel compaction (return `{ cancel: true }` with reason) when strict cap recovery overflows instead of silently skipping\n- `src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard.test.ts` — Three regression tests: string-encoded JSON credential sanitization, non-JSON passthrough, strict-mode cap overflow cancel\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### steps\n\nStep 1. Create proof script exercising production `extractMessageTextForIdentifiers`, `extractOpaqueIdentifiers`, `extractIdentifiersFromMessages`, `computeLostIdentifiers`, and `capCompactionSummary`:\n\n```typescript\nimport {\n  extractMessageTextForIdentifiers,\n  extractOpaqueIdentifiers,\n  extractIdentifiersFromMessages,\n  computeLostIdentifiers,\n} from \"./src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard-quality.js\";\nimport { testing } from \"./src/agents/agent-hooks/compaction-safeguard.js\";\nconst { capCompactionSummary, MAX_COMPACTION_SUMMARY_CHARS } = testing;\n```\n\nStep 2. Validate Fix 1 — string-encoded JSON args with credential `token` field:\n\n```typescript\nconst msg = {\n  role: \"assistant\",\n  content: [{\n    type: \"functionCall\", id: \"call_1\", name: \"configure\",\n    arguments: '{\"token\":\"deadbeef12345678\",\"endpoint\":\"https://api.acme.io/v2\"}',\n  }],\n};\nconst text = extractMessageTextForIdentifiers(msg);\nassert(!text.includes(\"deadbeef12345678\"));    // credential redacted\nassert(text.includes(\"https://api.acme.io/v2\")); // non-credential survives\n```\n\nStep 3. Validate Fix 2 — capping loses identifiers and recovery overflows:\n\n```typescript\nconst transcriptIds = extractIdentifiersFromMessages([\n  { role: \"user\", content: \"deploy hash a1b2c3d4e5f6\" },\n]);\nconst oversized = \"## Decisions\\nKeep flow.\\n## Exact identifiers\\n\"\n  + \"x\".repeat(MAX_COMPACTION_SUMMARY_CHARS) + \"\\na1b2c3d4e5f6\";\nconst capped = capCompactionSummary(oversized);\nconst lost = computeLostIdentifiers(transcriptIds, capped);\nassert(lost.length > 0);  // identifier at tail truncated by capping\nconst recovered = `${capped}\\n\\n## Exact identifiers (recovered)\\n- ${lost[0]}`;\nassert(recovered.length > MAX_COMPACTION_SUMMARY_CHARS); // recovery overflows\n```\n\nStep 4. Run `npx tsx proof-75336.ts` from the patched branch.\n\n### evidence\n\n```console\n$ cd /tmp/wt-75336 && npx tsx proof-75336.ts\n\n[Proof 1] String-encoded JSON args sanitization\n  PASS credential token value is redacted from string args\n  PASS non-credential endpoint survives sanitization\n  PASS hex identifier extractor does not capture redacted credential\n  PASS non-JSON string args pass through for extraction\n\n[Proof 2] Identifier loss detection after capping\n  PASS transcript identifiers extracted from messages\n  PASS hex identifier normalized to uppercase\n  PASS capped summary respects size limit\n  PASS identifier at tail is lost after capping\n  PASS recovery block exceeds cap (triggers cancel in strict mode)\n\nResults: 9 passed, 0 failed\n```\n\n### observedResult\n\nFix 1: `extractMessageTextForIdentifiers` no longer leaks credential-field values from string-encoded JSON arguments. The `token` field value `deadbeef12345678` is redacted by `sanitizeDiagnosticPayload` before the hex identifier extractor can capture it. Non-credential fields and non-JSON strings pass through normally.\n\nFix 2: When strict mode detects identifier loss after capping and the recovery block would exceed `MAX_COMPACTION_SUMMARY_CHARS` (16,000 chars), compaction is cancelled with a diagnostic reason instead of returning a summary with known missing identifiers. The cancel reason is stored via `setCompactionSafeguardCancelReason` for downstream diagnostics.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live compaction with a real model and conversation history (requires a running OpenClaw session with enough context to trigger compaction).\n",
